But no: if he had asked for legions, they would have been legions of angels. And what he did on the part of his authority, he did, not by human, but by divine ageney, even when he drove the money-ehangers out of the temple. For the seourge which he then used was a sign, not an instrument, of divine wrath3 as in other cases, the oil and the spittle was not the remedy, but the sign os cure. And to this pur- pose Augustino speaks on that passage of St John.
